Season chicken with garlic powder, 1 tablespoon soy sauce, salt and pepper if desired. Combine remaining soy sauce with broth, cornstarch, honey and ginger; set aside. Prepare rice according to package directions, using College Inn Chicken broth for the water. When rice is almost ready, cook chicken in oil over medium-high heat in large skillet, 5 minutes. Stir in baby spinach. Cook 1 minute. Stir broth/cornstarch mixture, and add to skillet. Cook, stirring constantly until sauce is thickened and translucent. Serve chicken and spinach over rice.